Test-First Enforcement:

For any bug fix or refactor:
1) Write/adjust tests first (unit for domain, integration for API).
2) Only then modify production code.
3) If tests are hard to write, explain why and propose the smallest measurable test.
4) Every change must include: (a) what breaks, (b) the test, (c) the fix, (d) why this won’t break others.
